The article discusses the President's remarks at the Congressional Hispanic Caucus Institute's 34th Annual Awards Gala. The President addresses the impact of the American Jobs Act on the Hispanic community and all Americans. The article highlights the progress made for Hispanic families, businesses, and students, but also acknowledges the toll the recession has taken on the community. The President's plan includes measures to extend and expand the payroll tax cut, cut payroll taxes for Hispanic-owned businesses, and put construction workers back to work by revitalizing schools and infrastructure. The plan also focuses on providing pathways back to work for Hispanics looking for jobs and opportunities for youth employment. Additionally, the plan aims to support Hispanic-owned small businesses and improve education outcomes for Hispanic students. The article concludes by discussing the President's previous efforts to support Hispanics in areas such as tax cuts, consumer protection, housing access, and healthcare.